FBIS4-32481 "dreeu123_b_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 BULGARIA Turkish Planes Violate Airspace; Forced To Land Turkish Planes Violate Airspace; Forced To Land AU2406164394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 AU2406164394 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Text] We just received the following announcement from the Press Center of the Ministry of Defense: On 23 June at 1040 [0740 GMT] the Air Force guard duty units noted a violation of Bulgaria's airspace committed by 21 light transportation aircraft flying from near the village of Radovets in Turkey, in two directions: Burgas and Sofia. The Air Force guard duty aircraft were immediately placed in a state of readiness, which included the takeoff of fighters. The aircraft that violated Bulgarian airspace were forced to land at the airports of Saratovo and Sofia. A commission appointed by the Air Force commander is investigating the reasons the flight regulations were violated.
